The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the strike on Monday that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, as rail traffic will stop completely and workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike until 13 hours.
On Friday afternoon the League Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike to be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Trade Union of Machinists will also be formed to coordinate Monday's actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while the participating unions will strike for an indefinite period on Monday, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for a strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
Based on the Monday agenda of the National Assembly it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on at very late evening hours, or perhaps around midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, significant difficulties will have to be faced in transport: on the railways work will be stopped indefinitely, in the morning a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the Volán companies may be stopped.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Railway Workers Union (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 13 hours will be on strike the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, the Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 in the morning, will hold a strike of four hours the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Trade Unions of the Educators called a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of the Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will take a national strike at alternative times and the Health and Social Workers Democratic Union (SDTSSS), which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal regarding public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into effect next year.
The third is to ensure, even before 2010, for advanced pensions, the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysing Division) of the Political Capital the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, from several points of view has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes can occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Gypsy problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "deteriorated significantly the image of Hungary abroad, especially as regards the stability and democratic development of the country".
They remind us that: from the autumn of 2006, the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups of Hungary received increasing publicity and momentum and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been formed in the country that define themselves as "national self-defence associations".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, of the army, that is to say of the state" - they add.
