The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the coming anus will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America parties are not unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holidays, state holidays and festive days.
The festive days are mainly related to religious festivals and historical events.
Let's celebrate the New Year also: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, a day commemorating the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th we celebrated the founding of the State, on May 1st the feast of work, on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased family and friends.
In addition, in our country there are two-day feasts of Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the holiday there is only one working day.
In exchange for weekends so long, on previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal rule is binding on all employers and their employees, as well as on public employees and civil servants.
It is not mandatory, however, for companies and service institutions which, because of their function, work uninterruptedly even during festive days.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24th practically stops life in the country, because according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
The next year several of our parties will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda will be changed around the work party so that, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that Friday, May 2nd will be a festive day.
The other change relates to the feast of October 23rd: on Saturday October 18th, we will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the year to come during the end of the year will be able to rest, since from December 24 you will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six little deterrents to embitter your colleagues' lives
