You borrow something that's not yours?
There's nothing more irritating than when you want to pick up a document, an office clerk or your phone and you can't find them.
Remember yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but by this morning it disappeared?
Do you find your missing pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Don't take anything away from your colleagues without asking them, because they'll no wonder be mad at you for taking their stuff away.
Don't take envelopes or post-it from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out of time.
You gossip about your colleagues' private lives?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Don't pass on to everyone the information (conjectures) you have about the particular lives of your colleagues!
Don't abuse your colleague's confidence when he shares his most intimate secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, although others also know the things about him.
Are you leaving on sick leave unreasonably?
