600,000 people failed to change their driver's license
Six hundred thousand drivers were passed the date and thus failed to change their old driver’s license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can apply for change so that officials will give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that hundreds of thousands of drivers will be on the roads after the New Year without a valid license.
According to traffic, the license has not been changed mainly by those who don't even want to drive anymore.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decline in the change of card, the metropolitan offices are full of requests and interest in the new card has increased.
The City Council calculates about 2,000 customers a day.
In the queues, half an hour is expected.
Around 140,000 drivers have not yet been taken out of Prague.
The issue of a new card lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must necessarily change their license and do not reach the end of the year, but will leave the roads without the valid license will risk a fine starting in January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can arrange the offence with a warning.
In the event of an administrative offence, the fine shall amount to SEK 2,500.
According to the above information, a fine could be paid to a person who is not going anywhere.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 kroner.
The Ministry appealed to the offices for moderate fines of up to 1,000 kroner.
According to the member of the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, the fines of a thousand kroner do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driver's license is a document in which people can decide whether or not they want it.
It is not the identity card that each person must have valid.
People who don't want to drive should hand over the driver's license.
Simply bring it or send it by registered mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the cards issued during 1964 and 1993 are no longer valid.
However, drivers will gradually have to change the other types of driver's license.
People with the document between 1994 and 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card that was issued between 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this is about 2.6 million more documents.
