What insurance do I need?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it's that, choosing the right car insurance is even harder than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is made in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the premium agreed upon in exchange for liability for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the more likely they are to suffer an accident, the greater the fee to be paid.
This is why both women over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Also, by using the recounts, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of mishap.
By increasing the frequency, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver has to study the situation carefully in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a number of disadvantages when it comes to purchasing insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the card.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is full risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a full risk free of charge, so that they can obtain insurance cover at full risk but at a more feasible price.
Such an agreement would require the customer to pay part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim contributed by the customer will be pre-established depending on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," specifies Luis Noguera, Spanish top manager of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will impact on the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate held by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After 25 years of age, drivers have it easier to hire insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
For this reason, the best thing is to hire a whole risk with franchise.
"Normally, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired when it comes to using themselves in an accident, and even when it comes to driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the customer is married but still has no children, it is preferable that he negotiate insurance at full risk, as long as his economic situation allows him to do so, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risks free of charge (this could be 300 euros), or, where a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a greater amount of franchise," says Luis Noguera.
For retirees it is advisable to have all-risk insurance free of charge (with this being 150 euros), or one extended to third parties when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
