After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" cast doubt on the authenticity of Brillo-Boxes of the year 1968 by Andy Warhol, the Moderna Museet Museum in Stockholm carried out internal research and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former museum director Pontus Hultén gave to the Moderna Musseet Museum, are false, and almost a hundred of the others of "Stockholm type", which are in circulation in the international art market, turn out as well.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Brillo-Boxes", painted the wooden boxes red, blue and white, with the same sample that had "Brillo" soap powder cartons.
According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his 1968 works at the Moderna Musseet Museum hundreds of Brightness-cardboard boxes were exhibited. These were not made by Warhol (due to expenses), but were brought directly from the "Brilliance" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but examples (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed producing in Sweden some Brightness-boxes of wood, but they were not exhibited at the Modern Musseet Museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of nearly fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Bright-Boxes" of "Stockhol type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions some of them were purchased for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the museum Pontus Hultén made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exhibited almost one hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already died for three years.
Lars Byström, the head of the curators of the Museum Moderna Musseet, investigated six Bright-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First they printed and embossed their tight silvers and then painted them in oil with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies of 1990 shows that the painting was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. Moreover, it is not about oil painting, but rather acrylic painting.
"These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and should be removed from Andy Warhol's official Brightness-Boxes list," says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet museum and adds that if The New York Authentication Commission "Andy Warhol Art" will not come to any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/exhibition objects."
Already in July the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" in which these are soap dust boxes.
But from that moment there everything remained in absolute silence.
The rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers who had barricaded themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered.
The ringleader Antonio Trillanes, who reproaches the president, corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter that he could not answer for shedding blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been entrenched in the building for a few hours.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, had a Thursday trial for having attempted a coup d'état in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, so he could suddenly deposit with about 30 supporters.
Evidently the military police who were to watch him had passed into their ranks and followed their mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blocked the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called for an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security advisor, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
"People are fed up," Trillanes said.
"We call on people to move into our ranks."
General Danilo Lim, who formerly led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said that soon the other military troops wanted to follow the march.
Great government critics called on Thursday for a major demonstration against the president.
For months now, his government has been reproached for corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the riot that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986 in the Philippines there have been at least seven attempted coups against the democratically elected government.
United Internet will be Versatel's largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of the telecommunication company Versatel.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price for a share is 14, 46 euros.
It has only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company's absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial share at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German market of DSL (Digital Subscriber Line).
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its stake to the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 by hundreds to 15.1 by hundreds.
In the financial market this means that the financial institution maintains the equity securities for a third party.
United Internet already in the previous day involved with almost 10 by hundreds the telecommunication company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the measure of capital increase has placed 17,4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106,4 million euros.
United Internet has bought 5.15 million shares of them for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, companies started negotiations on DSL-products marketing cooperation.
"We strengthen our collaboration," explained the spokesperson for the United Internet.
The two companies founded a joint venture MSP to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday United Internet reported that at first, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not make use of their right, i.e., they involve 18.49 percent of Freenet.
This meant that both companies maintained all options, especially the participation of the public limited company Freenet.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now the holding of United Internet and Drillisch had directly 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch will achieve the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the investment company Vatas was already agreed in August.
